      • getMappedInResult

        public final java.lang.Object getMappedInResult(java.lang.String url,
                                 java.lang.String tag)
        A method for getting data from MappedIn URLs by yourself. Note: This method runs on the the current thread. Make sure you are calling this method from a background thread/
        Parameters:
        url - A MappedIn URL
        tag -
        Returns:
        An Object which is either a JSONObject or JSONArray. Will return null objects if an error occurs. You can check exactly which type of object, use JSONTokener.

        Example: 

         
 Object json = new JSONTokener(getMappedInResult(url)).nextValue();
 if (json instanceof JSONObject) {
     // you have an JSON object
 } else if (json instanceof JSONArray) {
     // you have an JSON array
 }
